<main>
    <p>We are a private school located in Kabul, Afghanistan. Our mission is to provide high-quality education to students in our community and prepare them for success in college and beyond.</p>
    <h2>Our History</h2>
    <p>Our school was founded in 2005 by a group of educators who wanted to create a new model of education in Afghanistan. Since then, we have grown to serve over 500 students in grades K-12.</p>
    <h2>Our Curriculum</h2>
    <p>We offer a rigorous academic program that prepares students for college and careers in a variety of fields. Our curriculum includes courses in English, math, science, social studies, and more. We also offer extracurricular activities like sports, music, and art.</p>
    <h2>Our Teachers</h2>
    <p>Our faculty is composed of experienced and dedicated educators who are passionate about teaching and helping students achieve their full potential. Our teachers come from diverse backgrounds and hold advanced degrees in their fields.</p>
    <h2>Our Facilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Modern classrooms with state-of-the-art technology</li>
        <li>Fully-equipped science and computer labs</li>
        <li>Library with a wide range of books and resources</li>
        <li>Outdoor sports facilities for soccer, basketball, and volleyball</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Our Location</h2>
    <p>We are located in the heart of Kabul, just a short walk from many shops, restaurants, and cultural attractions. Our campus is easily accessible by public transportation and is a safe and welcoming environment for students from all backgrounds.</p>
